---
layout: game-base.njk
title: Eight Queens Puzzle
description: Place 8 queens on a chess board so none attack each other
pageCss: "/assets/css/queens.css"
---
<div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8 max-w-4xl">
  <div class="bg-base-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: #5741AC;">Eight Queens</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Can you place all 8 queens on the board without having them attack each other?</p>
    
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2" style="color: #5741AC;">How to Play</h3>
    <ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-gray-700 mb-4 space-y-1">
      <li>Click anywhere on the chess board to place a queen.</li>
      <li>Use the Check My Work button to see if any queens are attacking one another. Problems are highlighted in red.</li>
      <li>Click on any queen to remove it from the board.</li>
    </ol>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">If you find the 8×8 challenge difficult, try a smaller board first. The goal is to place as many queens as there are rows.</p>
    
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2" style="color: #5741AC;">Helper Mode</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">For smaller boards, you can turn on helper mode. When activated, all attacked cells turn red when you place a queen, making it easier to find safe spots.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <button class="btn btn-info start" data-size="4">Try 4×4</button>
    <button class="btn btn-info start" data-size="5">Try 5×5</button>
    <button class="btn btn-info start" data-size="6">Try 6×6</button>
    <button class="btn btn-info start" data-size="7">Try 7×7</button>
    <button class="btn btn-info start" data-size="8">Try 8×8</button>
  </div>
  
  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 items-center mb-6">
    <button class="btn btn-success" id="checkBtn">Check My Work</button>
    <label class="flex items-center gap-2 ml-4" id="helperLabel">
      <input type="checkbox" id="helperMode" class="checkbox checkbox-primary">
      <span>Helper Mode</span>
    </label>
  </div>

  <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
    <table class="queens-table mx-auto" id="chessBoard">
      <tbody>
        {% for row in [8, 7, 6, 5, 4, 3, 2, 1] %}
        <tr>
          {% for col in [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8] %}
          <td data-row="{{ row }}" data-col="{{ col }}" class="board-cell"></td>
          {% endfor %}
        </tr>
        {% endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</div>
<script src="/assets/js/queens.js"></script>
